    <h2>FIFA World Cup 2014 News</h2>
    <p>
        The biggest scoreline in the history of the <strong>FIFA World Cup</strong> qualifier - and indeed in the history of international football - was recorded on 6 April 2004, when Australia beat America Samoa 21-0.
        This legendary match also brought global respect for Archie Thompson, who got 13 goals and created a “world record,” which continues to this day. He still holds it as the single international record.
        And though the defeat ended American Samoa’s qualifying, so inspiring was the underperformance that it is now the subject of an acclaimed documentary, <em>“Next Goal Wins”</em>, playing across the world.
    </p>

